What makes it feel shoegaze (the “rules”)
These are the style invariants—use them to keep the repo coherent:
Field > subject (texture is the protagonist)
Soft boundaries (no hard edges unless it’s glitch/aliasing)
Layer stack (at least 3 layers: haze + grain + bloom; optional interference)
Nostalgia physics (light leaks, halation, paper/print/vhs memory)
For historical grounding: soft-focus + manipulated prints are central to Pictorialism (a real pre-digital ancestor of “shoegaze haze”). (Art Institute of Chicago Archive)
And the Orton effect is literally “sharp + blur blended,” i.e., a photographic version of “wall-of-texture.” (Iceland Photo Tours)
Riso / misregistration / overprint is a clean way to get tactile layering. (Dribbble)

