STYLE_OVERVIEW.md
# STYLE_OVERVIEW

## Definition
`shoegaze_style` is a visual translation of “wall of sound” into **wall of atmosphere**:
a subject implied through layers of haze, bloom, grain, and interference rather than crisp outlines.

## Core identity (the invariants)
1. Field > Subject
   Texture and atmosphere are the protagonist; the subject can be partially lost.
2. Soft Boundaries
   Edges dissolve; clarity is intentionally low; detail is localized, not everywhere.
3. Layer Stack
   At least 3 layers: (a) haze/veil (b) bloom/halation (c) grain/texture.
   Optional 4th: interference math (moire / phase drift / beat bands).
4. Memory Materials
   Film halation, paper fiber, xerox ghosts, CRT smear, light leaks.

## Emotional spectrum
- dreamy intimacy
- romantic melancholy
- nocturne glow
- nostalgia / memory haze
- overwhelm / immersion
- serene abstraction
- “silhouette in static” mystery

## Materials
- diffusion glow, halation
- film grain clumps, dust & scratches
- matte paper / zine / xerox residue
- chromatic aberration / color bleed
- fog volume, wet reflections
- moire shimmer / phase drift interference

## What kills the vibe
- crisp outlines everywhere
- clinical HDR, ultra-clarity
- sterile modern product lighting
- hyper-detailed “everything sharp” realism
- flat clean vector sterility
- overly readable poster typography


NEGATIVES.md
# NEGATIVES (what kills shoegaze)

## Global negatives
- ultra sharp, razor sharp, tack sharp
- clinical HDR, hyper clarity, high micro-contrast
- crisp outlines, hard edge everywhere
- sterile studio lighting, polished product shot
- clean vector art, flat design, corporate minimalism
- “perfect gradients”, “perfectly clean”

## Portrait-specific negatives
- overdefined pores, hyper-detailed skin
- hard rim light, beauty dish sharpness
- plastic skin, too much clarity

## Typography negatives (if doing album covers)
- huge readable headline text
- clean vector type, perfect kerning, modern brand identity
- billboard poster composition


