style/shoegaze.rules.md
# Shoegaze Rules (non-negotiables)

## The 4 invariants
1) FIELD > SUBJECT  
Texture and atmosphere lead; subject can be partially lost.

2) SOFT BOUNDARIES  
Edges melt. Sharpness is localized (if at all), never global.

3) LAYER STACK  
Minimum three layers: haze/veil + bloom/halation + grain/texture.  
Optional: interference math (moire/phase drift/beat bands).

4) MEMORY MATERIALS  
Your image should feel "recorded" not "rendered": film, paper, xerox, CRT/VHS.

## The “Shoegaze Test”
If you blur the image slightly and it *still works*, you’re in shoegaze territory.

## Common failure modes
- Too crisp: looks like modern editorial.
- Too clean: no tactile noise / no memory.
- Glitch too graphic: interference reads as vector overlay; must fuse into haze.


