Tiny compiler pseudocode (drop anywhere)
compiler/prompt_compiler.md
Given:
- subject (string)
- style.json (loaded)
- presetName (optional)
- enabledBlocks override (optional)
- palette override (optional)

1) Choose config:
   if presetName: use style.presets[presetName]
   else use style.defaults

2) Build parts:
   parts = [subject]
   for blockName in enabledBlocks:
       parts += style.blocks[blockName]

3) Add palette token:
   palette = preset.palette or override
   if palette: parts += [style.compiler.paletteFormat.replace("{palette}", palette)]

4) Join:
   prompt = parts.join(style.compiler.joiner)

5) Negatives:
   neg = style.negatives.join(", ")
   prompt += " " + style.compiler.negativePrefix + neg

Return prompt.


