# Model Tuning Notes

Shoegaze relies on subtlety. Different generators need different strategies.

## Midjourney-ish
- Likes poetic stacks but can over-clarify faces.
- Use stronger negatives for sharpness.
- If interference dominates: reduce interference tokens; let stylize do the work.

## SDXL-ish
- Responds well to explicit negatives + material tokens (film/paper/signal).
- Avoid repeating the same concept too many times; SDXL can overfit.

## Flux-ish
- Better with shorter prompts; use fewer tokens and rely on preset choice.
- Keep shoegaze glue (haze+bloom+grain) but remove redundancy.

## General rule
- If it becomes too clean: add "foreground haze veil", "film grain clumps", "halation glow".
- If it becomes too noisy: add "single sharp anchor detail" and increase negative space.


13) Style mixing rules (how shoegaze combines with other repos)
